body:
`iverilog` (default options) crashes when run on the following module which forces the constant evaluation of a function with out of bounds accesses.
```Verilog
module top;
    function automatic [2:0] f;
        input [2:0] i;
        begin
            f[0] = i[0];
            f[3] = i[3];
            f[3:2] = i[3:2];
        end
    endfunction
    localparam C = f(3'b110);
    initial $display("C %b", C);
endmodule
```
This issues exists both in v11.0 and on the latest master (6b127432da3ac848435200587a907738f6c3875a). Other simulators raise warnings, but simulate just fine and do not crash.

